name: Latina Woman
description:
The lines of my drawings go through stories and feelings, they twist, turn and compose an image that I then transform in my eagerness to express what I want. I use different tools to give it life, I like strong and contradictory colors as is my own chemistry. I like the surprise that generative art produces in me, which gives it a new life. Segment them whimsically, in a bold collage that has strength and visual impact, that says things and makes you feel. Maybe when I draw women I express the women that inhabit me...
"To become free, a woman must feel free, not to rival men, but free in her capacities and personality." (Indira Gandhi)
